Date: Thu 7 Nov 2019
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2019 [edited] https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=32323


Bluetongue, Cyprus
-------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Nov 2019 from Dr. Christodoulos Pipis, Acting Director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Rural Development and Environment, NICOSIA, Cyprus

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 30 Oct 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 5 Nov 2019
Report date: 7 Nov 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 7 Nov 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 20 Dec 2018
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 16
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (basic and advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Vrysoulles, Ammochostos, Ammochostos [Famagusta]
Date of start of the outbreak: 30 Oct 2019
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 105 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak 2: Dasaki Achnas Ammochostos, Ammochostos [Famagusta]
Date of start of the outbreak: 31 Oct 2019
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep, goats / 171 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 105 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep, goats / 171 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity / Mortality / Case fatality / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 2.86 / 0 / 0 / 0
Sheep, goats / 1.17 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, quarantine, control of vectors, vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal Health Laboratory (national laboratory) / Sheep / Real-time PCR / 5 Nov 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

